India Beats England by 126 Runs in Opening One-Day Cricket Match

-- B y   B o b   B e n s c h
-- 
2011-10-14T16:29:31Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-10-14/india-beats-england-by-126-runs-in-opening-one-day-cricket-match.html
India  defeated  England  by 126 runs
in their opening one-day cricket match in Hyderabad.  Ravindra Jadeja and Ravichandran Ashwin took three wickets
each as England was bowled out for 174 after being set a target
of 301. Alastair Cook top scored for the visitors, who collapsed
after reaching 110-2.  MS Dhoni was 87 not out and Suresh Raina scored 55 for
India, which reached 300-7 after winning the toss and electing
to bat.  The five-game series continues in Delhi in three days.
India was winless on a tour of England this summer, being swept
in a four-match Test series, losing a one-day series 3-0 and
dropping a Twenty20 match.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Bob Bensch at 
 bbensch@bloomberg.net  